      {
         "id": "13afeed9-c776-4b76-95f9-9e070ce3da1c",
         "name": "Folsom Culture",
         "history": [
            {
               "text": "#### Location\n\nJust like the original Clovis culture, the Folsom and Dalton sites are also located in the north of the *Abya Yala* (America) continent and are known for the artifacts found at the site (<htcite0>).\n\n#### Antiquity\n\nRegarding the antiquity of the population of these sites, it can be inferred thanks to the bones of extinct bison found in the region, demonstrating that the culture existed from at least <htdate0>. These data also confirm that the population focused on hunting activity (<htcite1>; <htcite2>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "8b923dde-4ced-4d70-9846-5bfa47d539c9",
                     "text": "Mark, Joshua J.",
                     "page": "Pre-Colonial North America",
                     "date_time": {
